The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are core topics in game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses practical applications such as supply chain, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new auction mechanism, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
